AXISengine Pre-Alpha Tag Reference
AXISengine uses a clean, plugin-style syntax to make scripting powerful and readable. Here are the main tags, directives, and modifiers you can use in .axi scripts right now:
Displaying Text
:show;() – Displays text to the console or log.
Place your message inside the parentheses.
:show;("Welcome to AXISengine!")
 Webview / Embedded Browser
Use the webview tag to open web pages directly in your scripts. You can customize the window with optional modifiers.
webview::hook-url(url, callback) – Opens a URL and optionally runs a callback when the page loads.
+dimensions(width * height) – Set the window size.
+position(x * y) – Optional: set window position on screen (planned).
+fullscreen – Optional: launch in full screen (planned).
+headless – Optional: fetch content without showing GUI (planned).
+resizable – Optional: make the window resizable (planned).
Example:
webview::hook-url("https://example.com", handle_page) +dimensions(1024 * 768) +resizable :show;
Plugins & Hooks
Plugins allow you to extend AXISengine with custom hooks and behavior.
plugin "Name": – Define a plugin block with a name.
def hook_name(args): – Define a function that runs when the hook is triggered.
register_hook(name, func) – Register a function to a hook (inside plugin system).
trigger_hook(name, args) – Manually trigger a hook with arguments.
Example:
plugin "FileLogger":
    version = "1.0"

    def on_save(file):
        :show;("File saved: " + file.name)
Modules / Libraries
AXISengine lets you inject built-in modules to expand functionality.
example:
inject {"utils"}
inject {"webview"}
Modules provide functionality like math operations, file handling, random numbers, and more.
Variables & Expressions
AXISengine supports standard variable assignment, math, and string operations:
example:
x = 10
message = "Hello " + "World"
result = sqrt(16) + pow(2, 3)
num = randint(1, 100)
!!::Notes::!!
Tags that modify behavior start with + (e.g., +dimensions()).
Tags that execute actions with webview::hook-url().
